cs.HC, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

The paper deals with predicting user behavior based on mobile phone usage logs, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of gradient-boosted trees and recurrent neural networks for prediction suggests that the paper may also fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). The paper also deals with information retrieval (cs.IR) in the sense that it is predicting which notifications will be attended to, and may fall under social and information networks (cs.SI) due to the large dataset of users and notifications.
